        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nFix the persistent Refresh menu row so it matches the surrounding menu actions more closely while preserving the menu-open refresh behavior.\r\n\r\n- Render Refresh, Settings, About, and Quit through a shared custom bottom action row when menu-card rendering is enabled.\r\n- Keep Refresh click and `⌘ R` refresh behavior persistent so the menu stays open.\r\n- Restore native keyboard activation for custom Settings/About/Quit rows.\r\n- Tune bottom-row spacing, icon size, shortcut placement, highlight style, and shortcut color.\r\n- Remove temporary debug tuning controls and stale intermediate row code.\r\n- Keep persistent rows resized to the rendered menu width during smart/cached menu updates.\r\n\r\n## Screenshots\r\nBefore:\r\n<img width=\"314\" height=\"118\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-23 at 13 55 05\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3b199bcc-c526-4336-b384-73bdca4a5dd8\" />\r\n\r\nAfter:\r\n<img width=\"311\" height=\"108\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-23 at 13 54 21\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d458443d-c7f1-49e8-b5c0-af51e97f88cf\" />\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\n\r\n- `swift test --filter StatusMenuPersistentRefresh`\r\n- `make check`",
